"{\"abstract\":\"The basic idea of shape from shading is to infer the shape of a surface from its shading information in a single image. Since this problem is ill-posed, a number of simplifying assumptions have been often used. However they rarely hold in practice. This paper presents a simple shading-correction algorithm that transforms the image to a new image that better satisfies the assumptions typically needed by existing algorithms, thus improving the accuracy of shape recovery. The algorithm takes advantage of some local shading measures that have been driven under these assumptions. The method is successfully evaluated on real data of human teeth with ground-truth 3D shapes.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"1401805077\",\"name\":\"Moumen T. El-Melegy\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1401805077\"},{\"authorId\":\"2496495\",\"name\":\"Aly S. Abdelrahim\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2496495\"},{\"authorId\":\"144773218\",\"name\":\"A. Farag\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/144773218\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2077597\",\"name\":\"T. Wang\"},{\"authorId\":\"2659763\",\"name\":\"T. Aoki\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1109/ICIP.2016.7533113\",\"intent\":[],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"008d2c3d5a6e95096e9de8a167f4b7f93a1ccefd\",\"title\":\"Multicolor removal based on color lines for SFS\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/008d2c3d5a6e95096e9de8a167f4b7f93a1ccefd\",\"venue\":\"2016 IEEE International Conference on Image Processing (ICIP)\",\"year\":2016},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2077597\",\"name\":\"T. Wang\"},{\"authorId\":\"2659763\",\"name\":\"T. Aoki\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1109/ICIP.2017.8296675\",\"intent\":[\"methodology\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"f7737d21595c885a8879f3b2104ac976c191788e\",\"title\":\"Multicolor removal based on color lines and improved hough transform for SFS\",\"url\":\"